==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: glass blowing
<hw>glass" blow*ing</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The art and process of creating glass objects, by
shaping glass when reduced by heat to a viscid state, using various
manipulations with the hands, especially by inflating it by blowing
through a tube. The process is used to manufacture a wide variety of
useful and ornamental objects. The manufacture of simple glass objects
has been automated, but complex glass objects are still made by the
traditional hand processes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glass-crab</ent>⟦br⟧
